section.t:
After receiving reviews and comments, changes of 01 version are shown as belows:  
        
        Rewrite introduction and add another goal of ATR as a measuring tool;
        Add section 3 indicating a ATR response. An bit in the EDNS0 OPT header is defined as a indicator of ATR response. The flag bit is called "ATR Response" (AT) bit;
        Add Section 4 Operation considerations, which discuss ATR timer , ATR payload size, and less aggressiveness of ATR;
        Add IANA consideration to register the AT bit;
        Add section 7 Acknowledgments;
        Append a list of references regarding Network reordering, and APNIC's study on IPv6 and DNS;
        Add Appendix A, An introduce of APNIC testing work and author's comments;
        Appendix B. Considerations on Resolver awareness of ATR;
        Change the category="std" . It is said in RFC6891 IETF Standards Action is required for assignments of new EDNS(0) flags. So the draft should be categorized as standard track if registering AT bit is desired in this document.
